Life threatening haemoptysis in cystic fibrosis: an alternative therapeutic approach [published erratum appears in Thorax 1991 Apr;46(4):274] 
 Desmopressin and vasopressin were used to control massive haemoptysis in a patient with cystic fibrosis.
 After bolus doses a continuous infusion of vasopressin was maintained for 36 hours and haemoptysis stopped.
